body.name: 214 Palmer Street : A completely gripping psychological thriller packed with suspense
body.description: No one was ever meant to see her at 214 Palmer Street....When Maggie sees the beautiful Venetian blinds moving in the Caldwells' front window, she freezes. Her favorite neighbors Cady and Josh are away, so who is in their house?The pretty young woman who answers the door tells a convincing story. She's Sarah. The house-sitter. Just here for a month. An old friend of Cady's who needed a place to stay. She's pleasant and warm, and Maggie wanders back to her house thinking she might have made a new friend. Yet she can't help but wonder why Cady never mentioned Sarah.What Maggie doesn't know is that on the other side of the door, Sarah is starting to panic. No one was meant to see her at 214 Palmer Street....A psychological thriller from number one best seller Karen McQuestion that will make you question what secrets your own neighbors are hiding.... For fans of The Girl on the Train, The Woman in the Window, and Gone Girl. Read more

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I haven't read the book yet, but I wanted to review and say that the book was delivered in perfect condition. I get nervous about ordering books through the mail, but Amazon took good care of my order, like always! This book sounds so good, and you can't beat the price of it, especially since I can't find it anywhere else.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It was a good book...I enjoyed it but it didn't have me glued to it or have me aching to get back to it, once I put it down

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars it was okay!
reviews.reviewText: It was an okay book. Not many twists, turns or surprises. I basically guessed the book ending early on. Well written story, I just wished there was more to the story.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Haven't even finished and I'm gripped to the book!!!
reviews.reviewText: I'm on like chapter 14 and while I have gotten lost a few times, the storyline is still interesting and easy to keep up with. I would call this a kind of slow read because with the first few chapters you get interested but it takes a couple of chapters to get into the juicy stuff and even when you get there it still takes some more reading. Would definitely recommend this book!! <3

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars a good book
reviews.reviewText: A good read, albeit for a moment it did lose me, but it came right back. Nicely tied up too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars love the ending!
reviews.reviewText: I enjoyed this book! It had me from the beginning all the way to the end. I really loved the ending! I had put down my reading for a while, but glad I chose to pick it back up, and then chose this book. Now I’m ready to start another one. One of my favorite authors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I enjoy crime stories, but this one didn’t grab my attention as much as the previous book I read. I know it’s not fair to compare, but that is my honest opinion about 214 Palmer Street. I couldn’t stand Clarice. I wish Gavin wasn’t such a tool. And Kirk should’ve had the balls to tell his wife the truth about what happened so many years ago. He was a weak character in the story. One that did not gain my respect. Also, Sarah was too much of a “goody two shoes.” Good read, but the characters annoyed me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It's an easy read, but not too hard to figure out and the characters a little too predictably stereotyped. Still a decent read though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on May 7, 2022
reviews.reviewText: A great read. I enjoyed it once it got going and read it quite quickly. Easy to read as well

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 22, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely loved this book even told a book group about it this morning. I throughly enjoyed it. With twists and turns I never saw coming. Me personally would definitely recommend this book to other avid readers like me.
The whole book seemed frivolous. The ending was terrible. Hated it. Waste of time.
Back and forth in time all through.A good enough story but a bit long winded ending

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 11, 2022
reviews.reviewText: What an excellent book… kept me guessing right to the very end… lots of twists & turns - Kept me reading until the very early hours… Recommended to anyone who enjoys a good thriller.
